Eliminate all of the opponent's cards.
Win the battle with your Hero's HP at 90% or above.
Eliminate all of the opponent's cards.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Hey, so what's you're plan now? How about we go save the world together, doesn't that sound fun?
Fun!? No, I have no interest in saving the world, I just want to be left alone to roam free.
Haha, have you forgotten who I am? This is your fate! You cannot change it!
What do you mean??
(Pointing) Look over there!
Grrrr
(Reading Poster) 500 Gold to the one who clears the deep forest lair. You don't look like a bounty hunter...
Yeah, business has been tough recently. I'm just barely scraping by. I only take on low-level tasks.
Don't worry. With your sisters help, you'll be able to take on even the most difficult missions!
My sister? I don't have a sister?
I mean me!
oh……

Levels.AchievementText: less than 3 cards in the cemetery.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Hey, can we just stay over here? That cave gives me the creeps.
Yeah, sure. I just won't eat in the future to save money. Or maybe I could just sell you?
NO!!! Fine…I'll go with you..
Were you not an envoy for the God of Prophecy? I wouldn't have thought you'd be such a coward…

Levels.AchievementText: Eliminate all of the opponent's cards.
Win the battle with your Hero's HP at 90% or above.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Finally on board! Zephyr Island here we come!
This boat has been commandeered. All you low-lifes get off the boat!
Who do you think you are？ Never heard of first-come first-served?
Haha, I am a nobleman. I don't waste my time learning your peasant customs. Now get off my boat!
Maybe this is a good chance for you to get warmed-up before we arrive on the island.
Well, nobleman, today I'm going to teach you how to kneel!

Levels.AchievementText: Win the battle with your Hero's HP at 70% or above.
less than 4 cards in the cemetery.

Dialogue.Dialogue: What are we doing next? Will it be difficult? When will we leave? I'm so excited I can hardly wait!
It's nothing really. I just need to deliver a letter.
Only taking the missions no one else will take, complete garbage, just like you…
I dare you to say that again!

Levels.AchievementText: At least 3 Two-star cards in the Deck

Dialogue.Dialogue: Where are we going to send the letter?
Zephyr Island.
Then why are we heading west? Zephyr Island is in the east! Do you have no sense of direction?
Hmm… Well it'll take longer but we'll still arrive there…
You can't admit when you're wrong, can you?
Shut up!!

Levels.AchievementText: Eliminate all of the opponent's cards.
Win the battle with your Hero's HP at 90% or above.

Dialogue.Dialogue: We are lost….
These appears to be tribal ruins.
This seems dangerous. Quick, let's get out of here!
Leaving already? You just got here, why not stay and play a while! Haha.

Levels.AchievementText: Eliminate all of the opponent's cards.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Thank god we made it out of there alive!
I was scared half to death!!
If you don't mind my asking, how old are you?
Hasn't anyone ever told you it's impolite to ask a lady her age?
…… Quick let's cross the river.

Levels.AchievementText: At least 2 Kingdom cards in your Deck.
Win the battle with your Hero's HP at 90% or above.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Can you do something useful for once? See my future, tell me of my riches! Or is acting cute all you do?
Why must you always pick on me! We are done. Help! Somebody help me! Leave me alone you big bully!
My lovely lady, who's bullying you? I can help you straighten him out!
Him! That's the man!
You have got to be kidding me…

Levels.AchievementText: At least 2 Forest cards in your Deck.
less than 3 cards in the cemetery.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Look, the clouds are really low. Let's stop on Tempest Island incase there is a rainstorm coming.
Is that where the name comes from?
No. It's rare to see a rainstorm on Tempest Island.
Then why is it called Tempest Island?
Tempest Island is controlled by pirates. The damage pirates cause is not so different from a Tempest storm.
…Are you talking about the boats behind us? Ahh, they are opening fire on us!

Levels.AchievementText: At least 3 Two-star cards in the Deck
Win the battle with your Hero's HP at 80% or above.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Finally! The South Harbor!
Amazing! No one will ever believe that you swam here from Tempest Island!
Before today I wouldn't either! Haha.
Tsk-tsk!
Pirates attacked and sunk our boat.  I had to swim here from Tempest Island
Yeah, sure. Next you're going to tell me you walked along the ocean floor to get here. HAHAHA.
I told you.

Levels.AchievementText: less than 4 cards in the cemetery.

Dialogue.Dialogue: I'm here to see your Dean, I have a letter that I must deliver to him.
I can't let you in without a pass.
Hey, where did you put our pass?
(Whispering) It was in my pocket when we were swimming, it's unreadable now…
(Whispering) It's a good thing the letter was enchanted, we should be able to restore it.
Hey! What are you two whispering about? Are you spies sent from another school? Guards! Get them!

Levels.AchievementText: Win the battle with your Hero's HP at 70% or above.
At least 2 One-star cards in the Deck

Dialogue.Dialogue: Guards? What's going on?
Captain, they're trying to barge in without a pass.
Wait, wait, wait! We have a pass. It's just... not readable. You can take our word for it.
Sorry, rules are rules. Though, if you can defeat our Arena champion I could possibly make an exception.
Deal!
Good!
(Whispering) Captain, does that work for you?
(With a sinister smile) The champ hasn't had a partner for days. How else will he stay in shape? Haha.

Levels.AchievementText: At least 2 Three-star cards in the Deck
Win the battle with your Hero's HP at 80% or above.

Dialogue.Dialogue: You!? How did you make it out unscathed?
Piece of cake. I barely broke a sweat.
Now, where's our pass?
…….No, that's impossible! You cheated! You must have cheated!
What? Are you going back on your word? Let's teach her a lesson!
No, spare me please. The man you're looking for isn't here. He left for Dragontooth Hill this morning.
Spare you? You must be joking.

Levels.AchievementText: less than 2 cards in the cemetery.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Who are you?
Sage, your excellency. We were sent here by the Adventure Guild to deliever this letter to you.
(Reads letter)Take this letter and deliver it to the Elven High Priest. Oh, and take this token. Do not lose it!
The cave in Dragontooth Hill has a shortcut to the Jade Forest. Run along kids! And say hello for me!
What! What is this? Another letter to run?
They didn't inform you? Typical. This is a continuing task. Don't worry, you'll be handsomely rewarded.
Hand… Handsomely  rewarded? Really, no joke?
I don't joke. Now go! The quicker you finish, the bigger the reward!
Hey Maddisy, what are you looking at? Let's go!
Well... (following to leave)
Aha. Run along, kids! Don't let me down! Ha ha ha ha(disappears).

Levels.AchievementText: less than 4 cards in the cemetery.

Dialogue.Dialogue: What's up, Maddisy? What are you thinking about?
Something doesn't feel right... The Sage was odd. Well, nevermind. First things first. I'm starving, let's eat!
Ahem!

Levels.AchievementText: less than 5 cards in the cemetery.
Win the battle with your Hero's HP at 80% or above.
At least 2 Two-star cards in the Deck

Dialogue.Dialogue: The Prophecy was interrupted... We will not be able to open it again until the next Fullmoon Festival...
Your High Priest, I swear I didn't break the token!
Fool, no one suspects you. Everyone knows you wouldn't be able to break the token even if you tried.
I seen a shadow of the Underground City in the well. Dark Elves must be behind this. Go and find out!
This sounds a little more dangerous than what I'm used to… Do I have a choice in the matter?
Well... by law, he who attempts to destroy the Holy Well is to be sentenced to 30 years of hard labour, so…
Wow, you sure know how to treat a guest around here. Underground City here I come..
Glad to see you that you understand. Here is a map. You'll need it.

Levels.AchievementText: less than 5 cards in the cemetery.

Dialogue.Dialogue: This is the Jade Forest?
I'm hungry!
The air is so clean!
I'm starving!
The scenery is breath taking! !
I'm starving to death!
The…
Stop it, you're doing that on purpose! Uh oh…

Levels.AchievementText: At least 2 Kingdom cards in your Deck.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Human, why have you come here?
I've come to deliver a letter to your High Priest. Here we have a token.
He looks like a girl......
Shh, Maddisy.
The token is real. (Looking at Maddisy.)
Though, I'm still going to fight you.
Why?
To see who the real girl is!
Maddisy! See what you have done!

Levels.AchievementText: Eliminate all of the opponent's cards.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Human, stop right where you are. Don't go any further.
My Sophist, they have a genuine token with them.  They are to meet with the High Priest.
In the wind I have heard the will of the forest. If you insist on going, expect to feel the forests wrath!
This is my mission.
If you do happen to make it through the forest. Heed my words. STAY AWAY from the Holy Well.

Levels.AchievementText: At least 3 Forest cards in your Deck.
less than 4 cards in the cemetery.

Dialogue.Dialogue: The forest is really bringing its wrath down on us! Maddisy, what's going to happen to us?
I don't know, but I have a bad feeling about this.
(Maddisy' stomach is rumbles.)
I'm so hungry I could eat a horse!
OK, fine. I'll go get you some berries.
Get me the sweet ones! I don't like sour berries.

Levels.AchievementText: At least 2 Three-star cards in the Deck

Dialogue.Dialogue: Your High Priest, they claim they have a letter they need to submit to you in person.
Your High Priest, this is a letter sent from His Excellency the Sage.
(Unseals and reads the letter)
"Ominous dark clouds float in the sky and thick fogs shroud the road ahead." We must consult the Holy Well.
(Whispering) We were told to stay away from the Holy Well.
(Whispering) Yeah. I know… what should we do?
Come on! Open the Holy Well!
Yes!

Levels.AchievementText: At least 3 Hell cards in the Deck.
Eliminate all of the opponent's cards.

Dialogue.Dialogue: The Holy Well is to be opened. She will tell us all.
Ahh! Why the token is starting to smoke!?
No! It's summoning monsters! Quick, Stop them! You can not let them pollute the Holy Well!
Geeze! I knew this plan wouldn't bear good fruit!
Do you ever think of anything besides food?!

Levels.AchievementText: Win the battle with your Hero's HP at 70% or above.
Eliminate all of the opponent's cards.

Dialogue.Dialogue: What is this place?
Look at the map. It should be the Charred Plains.
The Charred Plains? Are you saying we could be burnt here?
Haha, don't be silly. It's not just going to ignite itself. It's just a name, because its really hot here.
Look! Over there! There's a camp. We can finally eat a hot meal! No more stale bread! Let's go!

Levels.AchievementText: less than 3 cards in the cemetery.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Hey, little fellows, your journey ends here!
Huh~ This doesn't look like the Underground City?
Seriously? You see a Dark Elf and just assume we're in the Underground City? They are bounty hunters!
Eeeek! What are we gonna do?
Let's hold them off. The map shows an abondoned pit up ahead. Maybe we can lose them there.

Levels.AchievementText: At least 2 Two-star cards in the Deck

Dialogue.Dialogue: Did we lose them?
Hmmm…… I think so. Let's keep walking.
It's so dark. ...... Do you think there are any monsters in here?
Relax. Look! There's a firepit. And some pots. And sleeping bags …
Didn't you say this pit was supposed to be abondoned?
Ha ha ha, you two fools! You've walked straight into our camp, ha ha ha!

Levels.AchievementText: At least 3 Kingdom cards in your Deck.
less than 3 cards in the cemetery.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Whew! We finally made it out. Check the map, find out where we are.
Well, let me see ...
Got it? Hurry up or those bounty hunters are going to catch up to us.
Hmmm......
Do you not know how to read a map? Forget it. Give me the map.....
Awh…… I'm so hungry.
What does that have to do with reading a map? Stand up! Come on, we need to hurry.

Levels.AchievementText: Win the battle with your Hero's HP at 60% or above.
Eliminate all of the opponent's cards.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Hey! Hey! Has hunger made you lose your mind?
I can sense my Lords presence.
Seriously? Come on! This isn't the time for day dreaming. Stop fooling around.
I'm not kidding! Look over there.
You mean those broken lines? ... It looks like some sort of script.
It's so deteriorated I can only make out the word "liar".
Really? Amazing. I never would have taken you to be the scholarly type.

Levels.AchievementText: At least 4 Hell cards in the Deck.

Dialogue.Dialogue: It seems like we're in a temple.
... It is the Temple of My Lord...
Really? ... Look! They look like the mysterious scripts we seen earlier.
Well, let me see ... I still can't make it out. All I can see is "darkness" and "wood"
Do you think it's referring to the Underground City? It's covered in darkness right?
Yes. This must be a sign from My Lord.

Levels.AchievementText: At least 1 One-star cards in the Deck

Dialogue.Dialogue: Do we really have to cross the cemetery?
It's the shortest way to the Underground City. Let's go.
I'm a little hungry. Can we eat something first?
You just ate half an hour ago.
Ooops...I mean, we should rest for a while before we go.
Ok. You stay here and rest and I'll go by myself.
Hey! ? Wait, wait ... Don't go so fast!

Levels.AchievementText: At least 3 Forest cards in your Deck.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Whew! It's so hot!
That's why it's called the Burning Road. Hang on, we are almost at the Underground City.
Ha ha ha, I knew it! I knew that you would come this way! You won't get away this time!
Look what you've done now! You just had to choose the route with nowhere to hide!
Maybe if you could read a map we wouldn't be in this mess!
Walking aimlessly still would have been better than letting us fall straight into his lap!
...... Well, stop bickering. We need to make a break for it before they surround us.

Levels.AchievementText: less than 5 cards in the cemetery.

Dialogue.Dialogue: How do they keep finding us? Do these bounty hunters really have nothing else to do?
Oh boy, if you could fight half as good as you can run we'd be invincible.
Are you saying I don't know how to fight?
Ah, yeah, no! I don't need a map to know where we are now. This must be the Great Rift.
Amazing! You really are more intelligent than a 3 year old…
Oh, yeah like you're so great. I'm sure that's why those bounty hunters can never find us… oh, wait...
...... Hurry up. We are nearing the Underground City.
Yeah, you're just trying to change the subject.

Levels.AchievementText: less than 5 cards in the cemetery.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Why are we stopping? Dinner time?
It's always food with you…… I feel like we're being spied on.
Impressive, human. You have a very keen sense.
You have got to be kidding me. You really are an impressive bounty hunter.
I'm no bounty hunter. Nor do I care why you are here. Just do not interfere with my plans…

Levels.AchievementText: At least 2 Two-star cards in the Deck

Dialogue.Dialogue: Hey, what now? Another sign from the God of Prophecy?
...... No. It's just ...
Ha ha ha. What now you have acrophobia?
No! I just ... It's just my legs feel weak.
Unfortunately this is the only entrance to the Underground City. Get on my back, I'll carry you.
(Lifts Maddisy up and carries her on his shoulders)
Hey! ? Stop! No...... I'm not a bag! Put me down, put me down ~ ~ ~!

Levels.AchievementText: At least 3 Forest cards in your Deck.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Wow! So this is the Underground City? Huh? How are we going to get in there?
Don't just stand there. They'll spot us. Go over to that corner.
Didn't expect to see you again. I think the patrol men have spotted you.
Well, she is a traitor to the Dark Elves. A follower of the Gloom-girls. They wish to live a life on earth.
You! You're not one of them, are you? Well unless you want to be found, you'd best show us how to get out.
(Whispering) Did you threaten her?
I'm going to the Ebony Temple. There will be many guards, and priests of Lolth.
(Whispering) Isn't the Ebony Temple where we wanted to go?
Go, stay with her.

Levels.AchievementText: At least 3 Wilderness cards in the Deck.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Who are you? What on earth do you want to do in the temple?
Sneaking around like that doesn't make you appear like an honest man.
Don't be ridiculous. Is that not what we are doing? In this city those who walk tall and proud are not good people.
I am of the Gloom-girls Union. They have stolen something from us, and hidden it in Lolth's Temple.
It doesn't appear to be too heavily guarded, Why is that?
Almost all of the priests are at the altar. That's why I chose to come today.
(Pointing ahead) There! That's where we want to go.

Levels.AchievementText: At least 3 Forest cards in your Deck.

Dialogue.Dialogue: The altar is at the other end of the long corridor. We must part ways. Be wary of creatures in Shadow.
Thank you ... Goodbye.
I'd never heard of a good Dark Elf before today.
Well, she is a traitor to the Dark Elves, and a follower of the Gloom-girls. They aspire to live a life on the earth.
Ok. Well, why did she tell us to be wary of creatures in the shadows?
The long corridor is named shadow. I suppose she meant it's not as easy as it appears.

Levels.AchievementText: Eliminate all of the opponent's cards.
At least 2 Two-star cards in the Deck

Dialogue.Dialogue: Lolth's priests are over there. We're too far away to make out what they are saying.
Shhh…she doesn't believe something was Lolth's will so she will check with Lolth at the next ceremony.
Oh? How can you hear that? Impressive!
Jealous aren't you? ha ha ha
Hush, hush! Don't you laugh so loud! Shit! They've spotted us!
This is all your fault. We could have gotten more information!
Ugh. Like eavsdropping is so honorable? You're probably a gossip queen, aren't you?
Whatever. It has something to do with Lolth.
I don't think it's that simple.
Forget it. The most important thing now is to get out of here.
Planning on going somewhere?

Levels.AchievementText: Eliminate all of the opponent's cards.
less than 4 cards in the cemetery.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Hmmm...... What is this place?
Do you still have the map with you.
Judging by the map….Blank? It doesn't exist??
Which means we…
......We are lost again.
So tired. God. Will we ever get out of this wetland?
Stop complaining. Let's just hurry up.
I'm hungry... Let's take a break and eat something.
Be careful while you're eating! Maybe a monster will jump out at you from behind!
Oh no! Don't you scare me. I, I am….
Ha ha ha, what a sheep. You gonna stammer?
You! Look behind you! There really is something behind you..
Haha, stop bluffing.
Roar…

Levels.AchievementText: At least 4 Kingdom cards in your Deck.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Whoopee! We are finally out of that damned wetland.
The forest is still the best. I feel refreshed.  Let's have a picnic. Mmm dinner…dinner…dinner…
I know you love eating. But there's no need to keep repeating it.
I only said it once. There must  be an echo...echo...echo…

Levels.AchievementText: Eliminate all of the opponent's cards.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Look! A door!
Huh. How did I not see that...
There seem to be some words engraved here… It just says so and so was here?
Hey, don't touch it!
Relax! Look! Nothing happened. Don't be so nervous.
So... can you tell me why the hell there is smoke coming up over there?
That, uh, that is... run!

Levels.AchievementText: At least 4 Forest cards in your Deck.

Dialogue.Dialogue: What are those things? For everyone we kill, 2 more appear. Are they Paladins from the Kings army?
They seem to be some sort of illusion.
But it hurts when they hit me.
What doesn't kill you only makes you stronger! Watch out! Here come some more.
Kill them!

Levels.AchievementText: At least 4 Hell cards in the Deck.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Roar ~
Holy crap! The Jade Dragon?
What should we do? They are catching up to us!
Roar ~
We have no choice.
Then what? Run?
I hope it's not as strong as it looks. Attack!

Levels.AchievementText: less than 5 cards in the cemetery.
Win the battle with your Hero's HP at 60% or above.

Dialogue.Dialogue: It's not helping, they are growing in numbers!
We're running like chickens with our heads cut off. I don't know which way to go!
This place isn't even on the map! How can can we possibly know where to go?
I know.
Save it. Even with a map you wouldn't know which way to go!
I can summon the power of my God. But I will lose all consciousness. And once the power is gone…
It won't kill you, will it?
No! Is that what you want? It's just that the more power that's used up, the sleepier I'll become...
That's not so bad. How long will you sleep?
I don't know... But time is running out! Sleeping will be better than dealing with these monsters!
OK. Quick hold them off!
Which way should we go next?
Left.
...... Have you already summoned the power? It's offputting hearing you speak so matter of factly.
... Well, never mind.
Roar ~
Hey, you didn't tell me that we might run into this guy! What am I supposed do?
Fight!
This path looks weird. Where does it lead to?
Hea? Hea what?
Heaven?! I thought that was made up!
Go… Now.
OK…Hey, hang on there!

Levels.AchievementText: At least 3 Two-star cards in the Deck

Dialogue.Dialogue: Fluffy white clouds ... It really is Heaven! I never thought it was real.
...... Where are we going next?
Forward.
...... Geeze! I can't stand you like this. When can you return to normal?

Levels.AchievementText: At least 5 Hell cards in the Deck.

Dialogue.Dialogue: What a massive desert! Where are we supposed to be going?
Find .....the stela.
Find the stela? What stela? Where?
Running... out of….power.
Maddisy? Maddisy are you ok?

Levels.AchievementText: At least 3 Four-star cards in the Deck
At least 5 Kingdom cards in your Deck.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Finally, an oasis.
Mortals! Get out of here!
Ah! You scared me! Where are you?
Leave now!
No. I have to find the stela to save Maddisy.
To move on, thou must first pass my test!

Levels.AchievementText: At least 1 Two-star cards in the Deck
At least 5 Wilderness cards in the Deck.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Another ancient guard!
What are you doing in this land?
Oh. I'm here to find a stela. Do you know where one is?
There's the Shining Stela on the shore of Crystal Lake.
Crystal Lake, thank you...
But before you go there...
Yeah ... I know, I know. You can't just let me move on untested can you?

Levels.AchievementText: At least 5 Wilderness cards in the Deck.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Kid, I've been waiting for you. Turn right, and I'll meet you at the end of the road. (Leaving)
Psst! Is that an illusion created by His Excellency the Sage？
Kids! A demon has disguised itself as me. Don't be fooled by him. Turn left, go... (Leaving)
What the hell...Which one is the real one? I don't know which one to believe…
(Looks down at Maddisy in his arms. )
I'll go to Crystal Lake first.

Levels.AchievementText: At least 1 Two-star cards in the Deck
At least 1 One-star cards in the Deck

Dialogue.Dialogue: This must be Crystal Lake. It's so peaceful. I really hope there are no more ancient guard…
Thou are half right.
Naturally... What's wrong with the other half?
There are two more ancient guards!
Damnit!
So this is the Shining Stela. Now how will this wake up...
... Congratulations, you made it! Good for you! You didn't let me down.
Maddisy! When did you wake up?
Er…just now. Ah! It's been so long since I've had such a sound sleep.
I was so worried about you… Right, was this stela left by the God of Prophecy?
This certainly belongs to His Majesty. The epigraphy says we'll find the answers at the teleportal.

Levels.AchievementText: At least 2 Two-star cards in the Deck
less than 5 cards in the cemetery.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Hello, envoys of the God of Prophecy. I trust you have many questions for me?
Yeah. We are really in the dark on everything.
A follwer of Astaroth, the God of Lies got his hands on a page from the Book of Lies and chaos broke loose.
You mean the same book that drove Astaroth, the God of Lies, mad?
That book has incredible powers. Astaroth the God of Lies wrote the book and read it, and it drove him mad!
What about the Dark Elves?
They have been deceived and exploited by lies.He is trying to harness what power remains. Stop him!

Levels.AchievementText: At least 5 Hell cards in the Deck.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Kids, quick come over here.
Bah! Stop playing! We know your tricks.
What tricks?! Ahh, you must have spoken to the demon. Don't be fooled by him, it's a disguise!
(Whispering) Who is telling the truth?
(Whispering) ... Er ... Look on his palm. There seems to be some sort of magic signet... Watch out!
Ha ha ha, little fool. It's too late! Show yourself! Death awaits you.
Roar ~

Levels.AchievementText: At least 5 Forest cards in your Deck.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Ugh! You just got lucky! If I had just a little more time I would have summoned the perfect ...
Faker! Where is His Excellency the Sage?
Ha ha ha, do you honestly believe I would tell you?!
Well, let's just see how long you can remain silent!
Defeating an unsummoned character does not make you invincible! Let me show you who truly holds the power!

Levels.AchievementText: At least 2 Two-star cards in the Deck
less than 5 cards in the cemetery.

Dialogue.Dialogue: Wow, we finally made it out of Heaven.
Thank god we solved the Psuedo-Sage trick. That could have gone horribly wrong.
Ya think? We saved the world. I guess this is where we say good-bye?
You won't be rid of me so easily. I'm staying with you.
Alright...(whispers)I can't believe how shameless she is...
What!? What did you say about me?
I was just wondering which island this is?
Oh, don't try to change the subject!
Yeah, I don't know which island this is either. I suppose we are going to need a boat.
I know, I know. I'll start building one right away.
Just let me go cut down some lumber to use.
Hey, do you get the feeling these trees are watching us?
Do you think they know I'm about to cut them down?

Levels.AchievementText: At least 5 Hell cards in the Deck.
At least 3 Four-star cards in the Deck

Dialogue.Dialogue: Just looking at you I know what you're about to say... You're hungry again aren't you?
You really do know me.
OK, you just wait right here. I'll be right back.
I always feel like I should have 2 more brothers. A little pudgy one, and another to carry my luggage.

Levels.AchievementText: Eliminate all of the opponent's cards.
At least 5 Kingdom cards in your Deck.

Dialogue.Dialogue: This island is inhabited! Look, that's a grass hut!
Leave some food and eats!
Why are you saying food AND eats? Are they not the same?
eh… stop stalling! Quickly leave some food and eats! Or I'll be out of other options!
Is that a bandit?
